descript.abstract: World seas represents the boundaries for the major oceans and seas of the world. The source for the boundaries is the publication 'Limits of Oceans & Seas, Special Publication No. 23' published by the IHO in 1953. (http://ioc.unesco.org/oceanteacher/resourcekit/M3/Formats/Geography/OceansSeas.htm)
descript.purpose: The dataset was made in VLIZ for use in the gazetteer.

attr.attrdef: Unique identification number of ocean or sea according to IHO.

procstep.procdesc: Making of a waterbackground: based on the World Countries 2004 dataset was a waterbackground made. This is one polygon that contains all the ocean and sea features of the world.
Making the single features: based on the 'Limits of Oceans and Seas', the waterbackground was subdivided in individual features for each ocean or sea.
